<P>Little Bob likes playing with his box of bricks. He puts the bricks =
one upon=20
another and builds stacks of different height. ``Look, I've built a =
wall!'', he=20
tells his older sister Alice. ``Nah, you should make all stacks the same =
height.=20
Then you would have a real wall.'', she retorts. After a little con- =
sideration,=20
Bob sees that she is right. So he sets out to rearrange the bricks, one =
by one,=20
such that all stacks are the same height afterwards. But since Bob is =
lazy he=20
wants to do this with the minimum number of bricks moved. Can you help?=20
<P>
<DIV align=3Dcenter><IMG=20
src=3D"file:///C:/Users/WU%20YONGHUI/AppData/Local/Temp/Rar$EX01.525/p591=
.gif">=20
</DIV>
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A=20
name=3DSECTION0001001000000000000000>Input</A>&nbsp;</FONT> </H2>The =
input=20
consists of several data sets. Each set begins with a line containing =
the number=20
<I>n</I> of stacks Bob has built. The next line contains <I>n</I> =
numbers, the=20
heights <I>h</I><SUB><I>i</I></SUB> of the <I>n</I> stacks. You may =
assume <!-- MATH: $1 =9F\le n \le=9F 50$ --><IMG border=3D0 alt=3D"$1 =
=9F\le n \le=9F 50$"=20
align=3Dmiddle=20
src=3D"file:///C:/Users/WU%20YONGHUI/AppData/Local/Temp/Rar$EX01.525/591i=
mg1.gif"=20
width=3D88 height=3D30> and <!-- MATH: $1 \le=9F h_i =9F\le 100$ --><IMG =
border=3D0=20
alt=3D"$1 \le=9F h_i =9F\le 100$" align=3Dmiddle=20
src=3D"file:///C:/Users/WU%20YONGHUI/AppData/Local/Temp/Rar$EX01.525/591i=
mg2.gif"=20
width=3D101 height=3D32>.=20
<P>The total number of bricks will be divisible by the number of stacks. =
Thus,=20
it is always possible to rearrange the bricks such that all stacks have =
the same=20
height.=20
<P>The input is terminated by a set starting with <I>n</I> =3D 0. This =
set should=20
not be processed.=20
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A=20
name=3DSECTION0001002000000000000000>Output</A>&nbsp;</FONT> </H2>For =
each set,=20
first print the number of the set, as shown in the sample output. Then =
print the=20
line ``<TT>The minimum number of moves is </TT><I>k</I>.'', where =
<I>k</I> is=20
the minimum number of bricks that have to be moved in order to make all =
the=20
stacks the same height.=20
<P>Output a blank line after each set.=20
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A name=3DSECTION0001003000000000000000>Sample =

Input</A>&nbsp;</FONT> </H2><PRE>6
5 2 4 1 7 5
0
</PRE>
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A name=3DSECTION0001004000000000000000>Sample =

Output</A>&nbsp;</FONT> </H2><PRE>Set #1
The minimum number of moves is 5.
</PRE>
